FAQs Webflow Homepage Webflow Homepage Solutions environments with a single click Integrated Toolchain Use integrations or add your own Private SaaS Distribute your software on your customer environments Resources Case Studies Success stories from our customers Blogs Guides, Articles, FAQs Frequently Asked Questions Pricing Company About Who we are and what are our values Careers Why you should join us Docs Book a demo Have a question? Check our FAQs General EaaS Private SaaS Pricing Integrations Migration What are s key components (architecture)? Facets has two main components in its The blurprint defintions allows you to define your own software components and a control plane that enables to translate the blurprint in to managed cloud What does do for me? Facets democratizes a large chunk of your DevOps work to the Developers and enables the DevOps Teams to be Facets brings in workflows and tools so you wouldn t have to build from Can we run ourselves? Yes, you can follow https: readme.facets.cloud docs deploy-a-service to use Facets in completely manner in your cloud When is Facets not the right choice for a company ? For companies who are building static websites or building a product, Facets may not be the right There are platforms like firebase, digital ocean or various tools that are suitable for this How do I keep Dev environments in developer ? Facets provide various cost optimization strategies per Using compaction, spot instances and scheduled shutdown of Dev Environments, you can safely enable developer Can I choose a database in one environment and database in another environment? Yes, this is called flavors in For example, you can choose to use a redis in your QA environment and Amazon Elasticache in your production (from a single blueprint). Can I deploy a subset of the blueprint in an environment (Say Dev Environment)? Yes, you can selectively disable components for a particular environment . When do I need a EaaS solution? EaaS solutions are needed in the following 1) If you a SaaS company who wish to be present in multiple geographies or providing customer specific deployments 2) If you wish to strengthen your with ephemeral environments for efficient testing 3) If you wish to be . Can our customers have a shared access to the environment? Yes, you can configure shared access to the developer control plane as well as the environments for your customers and and enforce How do I deploy to a customer preferred cloud provider? Facets supports environments from a single For example, one of your environments can be on AWS and another one in How is Private SaaS deployments are different from regular SaaS? If you are distributing your software on customer premises (customer cloud accounts), you fall the category of private The difference between private SaaS and normal SaaS deployments reside in the level of Complexities arise because the number of environments becomes In many cases, you will have to support the preferred cloud provider of the Is there a discount for early stage startups? Yes, we have a perpetual free tier for early stage startups that can get you How are number of cores calculated as part of size? The number of cores are calculated as a running average of of the Kubernetes This statistics will be available on your Grafana What if I am building ? You may be eligible for a free facets control plane if you are developing a product for Please contact How do I integrate my existing application configurations? Refer to https: readme.facets.cloud docs deploy-a-service for getting started on application How much can I customize ? You can customize Facets to add new types of resources by adding a Terraform module that is written in Facets specified A detailed documentation is coming Can we shift from one cloud provider to the another? Facets eases cloud migration through the cloud agnostic blueprint However, other aspects like Data migration are out of We will provide the necessary directions in consultation with What kind of support from Facets we can expect when we are migrating? We generally a migration plan by studying your existing set Facets provide necessary support during the transition and How do I migrate to Facets with minimum risk? You can incrementally migrate to Facets managed environments from your existing Please refer https: readme.facets.cloud docs incremental-migration Help & Support If you have any additional queries, please contact our Help Center Send Email Get Your Facets Developer Control Plane Consult our experts for your DevOps needs by booking a demo Book a Demo View Documentation Linkedin Github Twitter GetÂ Started Book a Demo Contact Us Pricing Solutions Private SaaS Integrated Toolchain Resources Blogs Case Studies Docs FAQs Company About Us Careers Contact Us Terms of Service Â© Facets Cloud All Rights Reserved   Webflow Homepage Webflow Homepage Solutions environments with a single click Integrated Toolchain Use integrations or add your own Private SaaS

Privacy Policy | ByteLearn The AI assistant for math teachers and students Sign in Get early access ByteLearn Privacy Policy Effective Date: November 9, ​ ByteLearn (“we” or “ByteLearn”) is committed to protecting the privacy of teachers and This Privacy Policy will explain (i) what information ByteLearn collects from you and why we collect it, (ii) how we use and share that information, and (iii) the choices you have, including how to access, update and delete your ​ How we Collect and Use Information ​ Teacher Registration and Class Setup We ask for certain information when a teacher registers with Teachers must provide their full name and This information will be shown to students when they join so they are confident they are registering for the correct Teachers must also provide an email address and The email and password are used for login purposes to protect student data that only teachers have access The email address may also be used to send infrequent updates about The teachers must also provide information about the classes they are This allows the teacher to create assignments on a per class ​ Student Registration Students may only sign up for a ByteLearn account with a valid teacher code from a registered ByteLearn teacher, or the teacher can create their accounts by uploading their name, email, and password (optional), or by importing their account information from Google The email addresses are used for a unique login as well as password recovery initiated by the The only users that will be able to see the student personally identifiable information are the teachers for whom the student has The student s teachers are not able to see their students ​ Parent Registration Parents can register an account on ByteLearn with the intent of creating an account for their child or connecting to their child’s Currently, only teachers are able to create student accounts, but this may change in the ​ Assignment Data The primary purpose of ByteLearn is for teachers to put up assignments and for students to complete Teachers will create assignments, specifying relevant math problems for students to Students will complete the assignments and data will be collected regarding student This data includes which problems were attempted, the time at which each problem was attempted, the answers or individual problem steps the student submitted and whether they were correct, the duration the student was working on each problem, whether each assignment was completed on time and the completion percentage for each All of this data is available to the student s teacher(s) in order to use the information for student accountability purposes or to inform their The information is also available to all future, past and concurrent teachers added by the student in order for each teacher to understand their students strengths and weaknesses to the fullest ​ Automatically Collected Data We automatically collect certain technical usage information when you use the ByteLearn Services (“Usage Data”). Usage Data includes the information that your web browser or mobile application automatically sends to our servers whenever you The Usage Data collected in our logs may include information such as your web request, Internet Protocol address, operating system, browser type, browser language, referring exit pages and URLs, platform type, click history, domain names, landing pages, pages viewed and the order of those pages, the amount of time spent on particular pages, the date and time of your request, and whether you opened an Typically, this information is collected through log files, web beacons, browser cookies, or other device identifiers that may uniquely identify your browser or Teachers are able to see the IP addresses of their students for any given problem solved in order to ensure that multiple accounts are not signing in from the same computer possibly indicating one student is signing into another student s account to complete work under a false In addition, the ByteLearn Services may use third party analytics and bug tracking software (including, without limitation, Google Analytics) to collect further Usage Data regarding the online usage patterns of our users and bugs in our We may combine Usage Data with Personal Data in a manner that enables us to trace Usage Data to an individual We do not permit third party advertising networks or other third parties to collect information about your browsing behavior from our website for advertising ​ How we Share Your Information ​ ByteLearn does not sell or rent any of your, or your child’s, personal information to any third party for any purpose - including for advertising or marketing Targeted advertising is not permitted on We use the information we collect from you to provide you with the best ByteLearn More specifically, this information is used to: Provide and improve the Service, for example by developing new products and features Respond to your requests for information or c

PrivacyHawk is a privacy app that enables you to automatically control who uses and shares your personal It helps with opting out or deleting your data from thousands of companies, which protects your privacy and helps prevent malicious use of your How does PrivacyHawk protect my privacy? PrivacyHawk protects your privacy by 1) identifying which companies have your personal data, 2) helping you choose which ones to opt out of and 3) automatically makes those companies delete your personal data or opt out of having it shared with affiliates and third It also helps you mass unsubscribe from marketing PrivacyHawk also provides security alerts about breaches that may affect your personal data and provides education about the risks each of your personal accounts How does PrivacyHawk work? PrivacyHawk helps reduce your digital footprint, securing your privacy, which can lower risk of scams, spam, being hacked, and identity PrivacyHawk gives you control over which companies have access to your data and how they can use There are two types of companies that have your data: 1) such as data brokers and marketing companies (Data Harvesters) and 2) Companies you have a direct relationship with such as retailers (Direct Companies). PrivacyHawk automates deleting your data from Data Harvesters and gives you an easy way to control the Direct Companies use of your data such as deleting, making do not sell my data requests, or opting out from marketing Automatic Opt Out Process: Scan for Companies Using or Selling Your Data App scans for data brokers and companies with your first party For your first party data footprint, the majority of most people’s digital footprint can be found in their email PrivacyHawk securely connects with

Individual commitment to a group effort – that is what makes a team work, a company work and a civilization work Fun​ Work is only a part of your life .
